17 SECTION 2.
18 Said part is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
19 "10-1-393.20.
20 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
21 (1) 'Clearly and conspicuously' means a disclosure that is easily noticeable and easily
22 understandable by an ordinary consumer and displays any total rental price more
23 prominently than any other pricing information.
24 (2) 'Deceptive fees' means any fee for residential property, other than the cost to rent the
25 residential property, including any fee:
26 (A) That is reasonably avoidable or excessive;
27 (B) Charged for any service not actually used nor received;
28 (C) Related to providing any service the landlord is legally required to provide under
29 federal, state, or local law, or any rental agreement;
30 (D) That restricts competition, including, but not limited to, a fee charged for failing
31 to use a landlord's preferred vendor or service provider;
32 (E) That is not expressly provided for in the rental agreement; or
33 (F) That is designated as a deceptive fee with respect to residential properties by the
34 Attorney General.
35 (3) 'Excessive' means greater than the actual cost of a good or service.
36 (4) 'Governmental fee' means any tax or other fee imposed by any federal, state, or local
37 government entity, or by any tribal entity.
38 (5) 'Mandatory fee' means any additional fee or surcharge which a consumer is required
39 to pay for any ancillary services or otherwise as part of renting any residential property.
40 (6) 'Rent' means to lease, sublease, let, or accept a grant for consideration of the right to
41 possess and enjoy the use of any residential property either for a fixed time or at the will
42 of the landlord.
